UPDATE courses SET overview = 'Learning Outcomes: On completion of the course, students should be able to: 1. Understand the fundamentals of web design and development. 2. Create well-structured web pages using HTML5 and semantic markup. 3. Style web pages using CSS3 including layout techniques such as Flexbox and Grid. 4. Implement basic interactivity using JavaScript. 5. Understand the principles of responsive web design for mobile and desktop. 6. Design user-friendly web interfaces following UI/UX best practices. 7. Deploy and host simple websites on the web.

Course Contents: Introduction to the Internet and World Wide Web. Overview of web technologies and web standards. Introduction to HTML: structure of an HTML document, headings, paragraphs, lists, links, images, tables, and forms. Semantic HTML5 elements: header, footer, nav, section, article, aside. Introduction to CSS: selectors, properties, values, the box model, margin, padding, borders. CSS layout techniques: display, positioning, float, Flexbox, and CSS Grid. Typography and color theory for the web. Responsive web design: media queries, fluid grids, flexible images, mobile-first approach. Introduction to JavaScript: variables, data types, operators, control structures, functions, DOM manipulation, and event handling. Form validation using JavaScript. Introduction to web accessibility standards (WCAG). Web hosting and domain concepts. Introduction to version control with Git for web projects. Overview of web development frameworks and content management systems. Web security basics: HTTPS, input sanitization, and cross-site scripting prevention.

Lab Work: Creating structured web pages using HTML5. Styling web pages with CSS3 including responsive layouts. Building interactive web forms with JavaScript validation. Designing a multi-page responsive website project. Deploying a website to a web hosting platform.' WHERE code = 'LAG-CSC 104' AND department = 'Computer Science';